{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_46","type":"agent_message","text":"The tests point at the likely missing piece: `FnLoaderThunk` is supposed to load named function classes like `clojure.core$cons` through a bound loader. If those classes aren’t retained in the image, Clojure falls back to runtime class definition and dies. I’m decompiling `FnLoaderThunk` next to confirm that reflection/class retention, not legacy predefined-classes support, is the right fix."}}
